                <td height="622" valign="top" colspan="2" bgcolor="#004142">&nbsp;<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">Weweese dah sequet wehpohn!</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Rating</Font></TD><TD><IMG SRC="images/a4.gif" BORDER=0><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=2030"><IMG SRC="images/aread.GIF" BORDER=0></A><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=2030"><IMG SRC="images/areview.GIF" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=5124">Jonathan "Kantlearn" Kanter</A></FONT></TD></TR><!-- 5124 --><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">My thought process about the evolution of weapons and their use and how they are being used today. -Reguarding SWCCG of course :)</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Article</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ah, weapons.  The decidingly underrated card type in the entire game.  They have practically faded away.  Lightsaber&#146;s on the other hand have inherited the game, lets say, FIELD.  Somewhere we must really have decided its a more Civilized Time, because we&#146;re just not using blasters.  Don&#146;t get me wrong though, lightsabers are the most powerful weapon in the game.  Well maybe not...  Let&#146;s go back to that two lane memory...lane.  Plain old Blaster Pistol and Blaster Rifle were the weapons of choice.  When premiere first came out losing one of these things was very bad.  People used them.  As time went on and new expansions came out, people became more concentrated on strategy and decks that worked with &quot;tech.&quot;  People started to lose weapons as a part of the deck.  They couldn&#146;t &quot;afford&quot; them.  What were to happen if instead of battle interrupts to make battles go better, there were about 5-10 guns in a deck?	You would make weapons the theme of your deck and be able to get rid of the opponents characters faster, right?   Well, this has been much debated by my brain, and I have come to the conclusion of yes.  But, you need to be able to figure out which weapons will work, and which won&#146;t.  Imagine the US army, and no guns.  It just doesn&#146;t happen.  Now.  Forfeit zero weapons are great, but they need the right character to use them, thus handing you a bit of difficulty.  The point of the blasters are to bring the opponent&#146;s characters down.  You want to remain on table.  Now that you figured out the weapons, figure out which characters you play with and the rest of your decks.  Remember weapons first makes the deck more, shall we say, weapon oriented instead of well, say a mains deck that just throws in uh, Chewbacca&#146;s Bowcaster.	There are so many cards out there that enhance the effects of weapons and the weapons themselves.  DON&#146;T USE BLASTER RACK.  (this has been a payed political announcement)  You got cards that add to the weapon destiny cards that make cards lost when hit, cards that pull blasters from lost piles, reserve decks, used piles, I mean everything.  Then you have cards like crash site memmorial that even rescues weapons from going to the lost pile.  And now I reveal how weapons have totally evolved, everyone knows about it, Inconsequential Losses and Superficial Damage.  Now I know it&#146;s no real information, but people could use it and abuse it.  An endless cycle could be repeated with that effect, quick draw and portable scanner.  Weapons are very powerfull and should be used.  Clearing the site is good right?	Of Course!<br>
Now, space is a bit more difficult to discuss.	People use special weapons.  Most common are the SFS cannons and their x-wing counterpart, the laser cannons.  Capital ship weapons could also be abused with the new effect to make ships virtually unbeatable.  Who plays with Nebulon-B Frigate?  Nobody I know.  This card can be used with admirals orders and some Turbolasers will make this ship quite huge.  Blowing up the executor is quite fun as well.  Everyone knows all this stuff is possible but it could be woven into a deck much more masterfully then before.<br>
The point of this article was to show how usefull weapons are really.  It may not have hit right on, I wrote this kind of toungue and cheek.  Rate however you wish, I thought I would just tell everyone the possibilities of new decks, have a good time building them and be creative! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="articles.php3"><img src="images/aback.GIF" border="0"></a><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=2030"><IMG SRC="images/aread.GIF" BORDER=0></A><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=2030"><IMG SRC="images/areview.GIF" BORDER=0></A><a href="articleprint.php3?article=2030" TARGET="BLANK_"><img src="images/aprint.gif" border="0"></a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> </td>
